00:00:04.700 --> 00:00:06.020
Liking ourselves,

00:00:06.180 --> 00:00:08.900
having high self-esteem as we tend to put it.

00:00:09.400 --> 00:00:11.560
Is crucial to any feeling of well-being.

00:00:12.040 --> 00:00:14.540
What's odd then is just how unpredictable

00:00:14.540 --> 00:00:17.180
the allocation of esteem often turns out to be.

00:00:17.840 --> 00:00:19.440
There are people with modest jobs

00:00:19.780 --> 00:00:21.300
unspectacular bodies

00:00:21.300 --> 00:00:22.840
and unglamorous friends

00:00:23.380 --> 00:00:27.160
confidently nevertheless, they claim to buoyant levels of self-esteem.

00:00:28.340 --> 00:00:29.700
They seem to like themselves.

00:00:29.700 --> 00:00:32.240
Despite the absence of any vigorous signs of

00:00:32.480 --> 00:00:33.120
approval

00:00:33.120 --> 00:00:34.640
from the world at large.

00:00:34.740 --> 00:00:36.340
And then there are others.

00:00:36.460 --> 00:00:38.540
For who no amount of achievement

00:00:38.640 --> 00:00:40.480
prestige and financial security

00:00:40.580 --> 00:00:42.340
ever seems to do the trick.

00:00:42.340 --> 00:00:45.500
They anxiously challenge despise and critique themselves.

00:00:45.740 --> 00:00:47.960
Always feeling that they have under performed

00:00:48.280 --> 00:00:50.860
Never quite trusting that they really deserve to exist.

00:00:52.160 --> 00:00:53.280
Having sound levels of self-esteem

00:00:54.480 --> 00:00:56.460
Ultimately appears to have precious little to do

00:00:56.460 --> 00:00:59.000
with hitting any verifiable benchmarks .

00:00:59.820 --> 00:01:01.900
It seems connected up with a stranger.

00:01:02.180 --> 00:01:04.960
More internal, more subjective kind of logic.

00:01:05.240 --> 00:01:08.700
With factors immune to stand at notions of achievement.

00:01:09.540 --> 00:01:11.860
Three factors stand out in particular.

00:01:12.040 --> 00:01:12.800
Firstly

00:01:15.720 --> 00:01:19.160
The single greatest determinative of how much you will esteem yourself

00:01:19.460 --> 00:01:22.380
is how you compare with your same-sex parent.

00:01:22.880 --> 00:01:26.100
Whether you've achieved more or less than mom or dad.

00:01:26.760 --> 00:01:30.320
Rather brutally it seems that comfortable levels of self esteem

00:01:30.320 --> 00:01:35.140
are only available to those who've managed to outpace their same-sex parent.

00:01:35.400 --> 00:01:39.000
Those from a poor backround have a big unwitting advantage here.

00:01:39.320 --> 00:01:44.200
You might only be driving a beaten-up old taxi around Manhattan and living in one room in Harlem,

00:01:44.500 --> 00:01:48.900
but if your same-sex parent was a subsitence farmer from Easten Burkina Faso

00:01:49.220 --> 00:01:51.760
you will at times feel princely nevertheless.

00:01:52.240 --> 00:01:57.520
Similarly yet more darkly you might have grown up in ostensibly privilege circumstances,

00:01:57.800 --> 00:02:03.280
but if you same-sex parent made a few hundred milion and you're only managing to pull in a midlle-class salary

00:02:03.660 --> 00:02:08.720
you're liable never quite to shake of haunting feeling that you're a disgrace

00:02:09.480 --> 00:02:10.160
Secondly

00:02:12.500 --> 00:02:16.360
We don't feel inadequate in relation to everyone who has more than US

00:02:16.660 --> 00:02:21.780
only those who we'we come to see as belonging to another crucial determinative self-esteem.

